review_blob: UPDATED: MAY 4, 2014

Beautiful clear amber with great lacing. Aromas of pine, citrus, and grass. A bit harsh hop profile with a descent amount of malt and alcohol. A fresh IPA that tastes as it smells. Bitter with a nice creamy mouthfeel. Good.

Hazy orange. No head but nice lacing.
Aroma of honey, pine, floral with tropical fruits. The taste is the same with a nice bite of bitterness and a nice malty backbone. ABV well hidden. Great stuff!

Black ale with a huge beige head. Aroma of coffe, caramel, liqorice and roasted malts. The taste is chocolate, coffe, hops, some malty sweetness and liqorice. The taste ends with a pleasant bitterness. Good but there are other stouts out there that are much better.
beer_name: Smuttynose Big Beer Series: Imperial Stout

review_blob: Ok compared to some other beers in the cheap pricerange. Malty cardboard in the nose. The taste is similar with a malty sweetness and a weak tone of hops.

beer_brewer_name: Schneider Weisse G. Schneider & Sohn GmbH
review_blob: Do not have to say much more about this masterpiece than that it is one of the best beers I have ever tasted! Period!!!
Brown and clear beer. Something belgian in the nose with light smokey notes. Taste of sweet malts. Grains, raisins, figs, light smoke and some spices. Well made but uninteresting.

beer_brewer_name: Schneider Weisse G. Schneider & Sohn GmbH
review_blob: Eye: hazy, amber/gold. Nose: banana, bread, yeast, spice. Taste: hops, bread, yeast, cloves and so on. More bitterness than any Hefe I have tasted. Brilliant!
Aggressive pour gives me a black beer with a beige two finger head. Aroma of pine and roasted malt with a fruity touch. Tastes as it smells. Smooth, bitter and a little dry. I like this beer.

Murky brown liquid the glass. Small beige head. Figs, brown sugar, raisins and bread in the nose. Tastes brown sugar, yeast, dark bread, dark fruits, syrup and some alcohol. It has a sweet and sticky mouthfeel with low carbonation. This is one of my favourite belgian ales. Its complexity makes it a winner in its style for me. Great brew!
Spicearama. Brown ale with nice lacing. Sweet and spicy aroma. Reminds me of Christmas. Taste of smoke, classical christmas spices, some pumpkin. A little too sweet. Ok, but I would not buy it again.
beer_name: Samuel Adams Fat Jack Double Pumpkin

review_blob: A little hazy. Small head that vanishes fast. Aroma of passionfruit, pine, citrus, honey. Tastes as it smells.Powerfull lingering bitterness with fruit and alcohol. Nice but not more than that.

First rate. Pours a nice big head that disappears fast. Smell: Pine, tropical fruits, sweet malts and citrus. Taste: Citrus, pine tree, sweet caramel, some tropical juice, great bitterness. Complex. Mouthfeel: Nice high bitternes, a little sweet but not cloying, no alcoholburn. Good water quality. Nice soft carbonation. Glad having this as my first rate. A great example of an American IPA
